      "5.       Covid killed 22 mln people worldwide.",
      "6.       Opium use has destroyed whole communities that might have otherwise yielded job seekers.",
      "7.       The education system is not teaching the right syllabus. We need programmers, engineers, and scientists. We should focus more of our tax dollars to incentivize people to study what we need and pay them meaningful salaries that will repay their incurred investment and not further burden the taxpayer.",
      "8.       In addition it would be helpful if there were trade schools of many different orientations to turn out necessary skills such as plumbers, electricians, and the like rather than degrees that do nothing to prepare future workers for the needs of our society.",
      "So as the above list suggests this problem is going to get a lot worse and none of these trends, with the possible exception of Covid, is going to do other than grow as a contributory factor. Plus let’s remember China is on the cusp of the mortality problem the rest of the world has already experienced with Covid.",
